1
00:01:00,083 --> 00:01:02,840
[Episode 16: The pretty girl who buys you food]

2
00:02:01,125 --> 00:02:03,012
[Please give me a call when you wake up]

3
00:02:04,782 --> 00:02:06,984
It's 9 already?

4
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:12,582
Writer Kim.

5
00:02:12,582 --> 00:02:13,958
<i>Hey, Na Hui.</i>

6
00:02:13,958 --> 00:02:15,960
I'm so sorry, did I wake you?

7
00:02:15,960 --> 00:02:18,838
No, I was already up.

8
00:02:18,838 --> 00:02:20,173
<i>This early?</i>

9
00:02:20,173 --> 00:02:21,864
Yeah, what's up?

10
00:02:22,917 --> 00:02:25,220
I wanted to ask
when works for next week's meeting.

11
00:02:25,220 --> 00:02:28,348
PD Shin wanted to know.

12
00:02:28,348 --> 00:02:31,142
He could just ask me directly.

13
00:02:31,142 --> 00:02:33,311
He was worried about interrupting your writing.

14
00:02:33,311 --> 00:02:34,854
I'm on a roll right now.

15
00:02:34,854 --> 00:02:37,065
I'll probably finish episode 15 today.

16
00:02:37,065 --> 00:02:38,191
Let's meet tomorrow.

17
00:02:38,191 --> 00:02:39,985
<i>You're already on episode 15?</i>

18
00:02:39,985 --> 00:02:42,149
Yeah, I finally got some momentum going.

19
00:02:42,792 --> 00:02:44,822
That's amazing.

20
00:02:44,822 --> 00:02:46,783
But did you pull an all-nighter?

21
00:02:46,783 --> 00:02:48,701
No, I got a little sleep.

22
00:02:48,701 --> 00:02:50,537
Can I do anything for you?

23
00:02:50,537 --> 00:02:52,458
<i>No, it's the weekend. Take it easy.</i>

24
00:02:52,458 --> 00:02:53,831
<i>I'll call you if I need anything.</i>

25
00:02:53,831 --> 00:02:55,959
Sure thing.

26
00:02:55,959 --> 00:02:57,585
You got this!

27
00:02:57,585 --> 00:02:59,286
You can do it!

28
00:03:01,339 --> 00:03:04,467
How is she cranking this out
so fast all of a sudden?

29
00:03:04,467 --> 00:03:06,460
That's crazy.

30
00:03:09,583 --> 00:03:10,875
How nice is this?

31
00:03:10,875 --> 00:03:12,993
Now this is normal.

32
00:03:24,958 --> 00:03:27,333
Look how calm everything is in here.

33
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:30,702
I could almost thank PD Shin
for drawing the line.

34
00:03:30,702 --> 00:03:34,280
When I think
about all those weeks we threw away,

35
00:03:35,498 --> 00:03:38,158
it really grinds my gears.

36
00:03:46,208 --> 00:03:47,917
What's going on?

37
00:03:51,083 --> 00:03:52,950
What is it?

38
00:03:59,042 --> 00:04:01,472
Oh come on, what now?

39
00:04:02,191 --> 00:04:03,567
Today is Sunday.

40
00:04:03,567 --> 00:04:05,611
It's the day PD Shin has his blind date.

41
00:04:05,611 --> 00:04:07,333
So what?

42
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:10,106
What if it goes well?

43
00:04:12,784 --> 00:04:14,161
Whose idea was this again?

44
00:04:14,161 --> 00:04:16,497
Yumi arranged it, so what's the big deal?

45
00:04:16,497 --> 00:04:18,290
It's your fault.

46
00:04:18,290 --> 00:04:21,117
You, Pride Cell!

47
00:04:21,960 --> 00:04:25,047
What, PD Shin draws a clear line
and I do nothing?

48
00:04:25,047 --> 00:04:27,007
All you had to say was you'd look around.

49
00:04:27,007 --> 00:04:28,842
Nobody told you to actually arrange one!

50
00:04:28,842 --> 00:04:31,178
And that's how I protected Yumi's dignity.

51
00:04:31,178 --> 00:04:32,846
She went through with it for real.

52
00:04:32,846 --> 00:04:34,181
It's because of my good call

53
00:04:34,181 --> 00:04:36,792
that Yumi held on to the last of her pride.

54
00:04:36,792 --> 00:04:38,250
Don't forget it, guys.

55
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:40,687
"If you don't want me,

56
00:04:40,687 --> 00:04:43,774
then I don't want you either!"

57
00:04:43,774 --> 00:04:46,184
Just zip it, would you!

58
00:04:49,208 --> 00:04:51,625
Why don't you shut your mouth first?

59
00:04:58,872 --> 00:05:02,283
There are only a few hours left now.

60
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:09,325
I feel like I'm boiling inside.

61
00:05:10,801 --> 00:05:12,844
Like something's going to burst,

62
00:05:12,844 --> 00:05:16,256
you know, that bubbly, restless feeling?

63
00:05:17,375 --> 00:05:19,500
What's wrong with her?

64
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:24,625
Love Cell is acting weird.

65
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:27,035
She looks like she's about to blow.

66
00:05:28,235 --> 00:05:30,904
Don't you come over here!

67
00:05:30,904 --> 00:05:32,197
Serves you right.

68
00:05:32,197 --> 00:05:34,199
I saw this coming a mile away.

69
00:05:34,199 --> 00:05:37,077
We have a deadline breathing down our necks,
why go all the way to Busan?

70
00:05:37,077 --> 00:05:38,662
And what did that trip get us?

71
00:05:38,662 --> 00:05:42,115
All that effort just to arrange a blind date?

72
00:05:43,083 --> 00:05:44,418
No.

73
00:05:44,418 --> 00:05:45,458
Every bit of energy

74
00:05:45,458 --> 00:05:48,333
can be channeled into another form.

75
00:05:50,257 --> 00:05:52,633
Come over here, Love Cell.

76
00:05:52,633 --> 00:05:55,303
Come with me.

77
00:05:55,303 --> 00:05:58,792
Let's use that lovesick energy for the story.

78
00:05:58,792 --> 00:06:02,083
Go ahead, pour your heart out.

79
00:06:02,083 --> 00:06:04,417
Wait, not here.

80
00:06:20,042 --> 00:06:23,581
Yes, here it comes, I can feel it.

81
00:06:23,581 --> 00:06:26,492
The feelings are rushing in like crazy!

82
00:06:46,604 --> 00:06:48,189
Not bad at all, huh?

83
00:06:48,189 --> 00:06:49,992
This is good.

84
00:06:54,904 --> 00:06:57,272
Could I actually be a genius?

85
00:07:09,375 --> 00:07:12,458
<i>Guess where I am right now!</i>

86
00:07:22,390 --> 00:07:25,008
Wait, this looks like my neighborhood.

87
00:07:28,042 --> 00:07:30,458
[Wait, this looks like my neighborhood]

88
00:07:30,458 --> 00:07:31,667
<i>That's right.</i>

89
00:07:31,667 --> 00:07:33,458
<i>I'm in your neighborhood.</i>

90
00:07:33,458 --> 00:07:36,408
<i>PD Shin and I are meeting up here.</i>

91
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:39,156
<i>What are you doing all the way over here?</i>

92
00:07:39,156 --> 00:07:41,750
<i>Why not just meet in Seoul?</i>

93
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:43,958
<i>I had a thing for work in Ilsan earlier,</i>

94
00:07:43,958 --> 00:07:46,292
<i>so I said meeting here was easier.</i>

95
00:07:46,292 --> 00:07:48,042
<i>I'll fill you in once we're done!</i>

96
00:07:48,042 --> 00:07:49,834
You don't need to do all that.

97
00:07:49,834 --> 00:07:51,625
<i>No need for that, just enjoy your...</i>

98
00:07:51,625 --> 00:07:53,583
<i>Oh! He just showed up.</i>

99
00:07:53,583 --> 00:07:56,500
[Oh! He just showed up]
[No need for that, just enjoy your...]

100
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:59,542
<i>Oh my gosh, he's cuter in real life!</i>

101
00:07:59,542 --> 00:08:01,950
<i>I'll text you after!</i>

102
00:08:11,083 --> 00:08:12,766
<i>They met. They actually met.</i>

103
00:08:12,766 --> 00:08:14,066
<i>They finally met.</i>

104
00:08:14,066 --> 00:08:15,292
<i>Just forget about it.</i>

105
00:08:15,292 --> 00:08:17,792
<i>We were on fire just a second ago.</i>

106
00:08:17,792 --> 00:08:19,617
<i>Let's get back to it.</i>

107
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:27,000
<i>But don't you want to eat something?</i>

108
00:08:31,042 --> 00:08:33,358
Hey, Hungry Cell, you're hungry, right?

109
00:08:33,358 --> 00:08:34,375
What?

110
00:08:34,375 --> 00:08:37,033
How about we grab a bite first?

111
00:08:38,298 --> 00:08:40,258
But I'm not hungry?

112
00:08:40,258 --> 00:08:41,968
I ate late-night snacks all night long.

113
00:08:41,968 --> 00:08:43,750
Come on, you want something sweet.

114
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:46,681
I had watermelon juice earlier so I don't...

115
00:08:46,681 --> 00:08:48,767
Not craving sugar? How is that possible?

116
00:08:48,767 --> 00:08:52,658
You always have a sweet tooth, why not today?

117
00:08:56,775 --> 00:08:58,617
I'm craving sweets now.

118
00:08:59,611 --> 00:09:01,325
Let's grab a snack.

119
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:09,375
<i>First floor.</i>

120
00:09:14,584 --> 00:09:17,292
<i>Cancel first floor, basement level 2.</i>

121
00:09:17,292 --> 00:09:20,283
Wait, I thought
we were hitting the convenience store?

122
00:09:26,221 --> 00:09:28,667
Where are we going for a snack?

123
00:09:28,667 --> 00:09:33,436
I'm craving Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang
so bad right now.

124
00:09:33,436 --> 00:09:36,356
Hold on, what? She's heading home?

125
00:09:36,356 --> 00:09:37,649
Just to get bungeoppang?

126
00:09:37,649 --> 00:09:39,192
I can't believe this.

127
00:09:39,192 --> 00:09:41,450
She left without her car keys...

128
00:09:44,573 --> 00:09:47,033
Who's got the car keys?

129
00:09:52,167 --> 00:09:54,749
It's only a 10-minute walk, no big deal.

130
00:09:54,749 --> 00:09:57,492
I just need some fresh air anyway.

131
00:09:58,325 --> 00:10:01,200
I really pushed myself too hard.

132
00:10:31,333 --> 00:10:32,912
I really pushed myself too hard.

133
00:10:32,912 --> 00:10:35,325
Isn't that the place right there?

134
00:10:37,750 --> 00:10:40,200
I knew it.

135
00:10:50,971 --> 00:10:52,389
They're really on their date.

136
00:10:52,389 --> 00:10:54,015
Well, of course they are.

137
00:10:54,015 --> 00:10:55,792
No kidding, Captain Obvious.

138
00:10:55,792 --> 00:10:57,917
Jenny really dressed up today.

139
00:10:57,917 --> 00:10:59,646
She put a lot of effort into her makeup.

140
00:10:59,646 --> 00:11:01,940
She nailed those curls.

141
00:11:01,940 --> 00:11:04,125
They look good together.

142
00:11:04,125 --> 00:11:05,250
Let's go already.

143
00:11:05,250 --> 00:11:07,028
We were supposed to wrap up today.

144
00:11:07,028 --> 00:11:08,167
Come on, Yumi.

145
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:10,617
You might get a parking ticket.

146
00:11:16,580 --> 00:11:18,790
- What?
- Oh no, she saw us.

147
00:11:18,790 --> 00:11:20,700
Yumi!

148
00:11:27,841 --> 00:11:29,658
Yumi.

149
00:11:33,667 --> 00:11:35,682
What is this? This isn't right.

150
00:11:35,682 --> 00:11:38,667
And do you realize Yumi hasn't even washed up?

151
00:11:38,667 --> 00:11:40,792
She looks like a hot mess right now!

152
00:11:40,792 --> 00:11:42,731
Let's get out of here, run!

153
00:11:42,731 --> 00:11:45,150
Everyone, relax.

154
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:47,875
She's not just some regular Kim Yumi now.

155
00:11:47,875 --> 00:11:49,988
She's a celebrity author, Kim Yumi.

156
00:11:49,988 --> 00:11:52,491
Writer Kim's got a reputation to keep.

157
00:11:52,491 --> 00:11:54,583
And how exactly?

158
00:11:54,583 --> 00:11:56,294
Yumi has just one play here,

159
00:11:56,294 --> 00:11:58,658
and this is it.

160
00:12:11,167 --> 00:12:12,260
Oh, hey Jenny.

161
00:12:12,260 --> 00:12:13,625
Yumi.

162
00:12:13,625 --> 00:12:14,804
Hello.

163
00:12:14,804 --> 00:12:17,000
Hello.

164
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,808
I was in the neighborhood,

165
00:12:18,808 --> 00:12:22,145
your photo popped in my head, so I looked in.

166
00:12:22,145 --> 00:12:24,083
Wanted to see how things were going.

167
00:12:24,083 --> 00:12:25,649
Well, looks like I got busted.

168
00:12:25,649 --> 00:12:27,708
I figured you'd be at the studio!

169
00:12:27,708 --> 00:12:29,778
I stopped by for some bungeoppang.

170
00:12:29,778 --> 00:12:32,408
Nowhere else makes it right.

171
00:12:33,375 --> 00:12:35,200
So, having something tasty?

172
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:37,667
Yes, we're having pasta.

173
00:12:37,667 --> 00:12:38,703
What about your lunch?

174
00:12:38,703 --> 00:12:40,497
Obviously, yeah.

175
00:12:40,497 --> 00:12:42,250
Anyway, you two enjoy your time.

176
00:12:42,250 --> 00:12:43,542
Wait.

177
00:12:43,542 --> 00:12:44,834
Stay for just a bit!

178
00:12:44,834 --> 00:12:47,583
Hey, I know when I'm a third wheel.

179
00:12:47,583 --> 00:12:50,340
Seriously though, you two look so good today.

180
00:12:50,340 --> 00:12:53,542
I barely recognize you guys!

181
00:12:53,542 --> 00:12:54,542
Hey.

182
00:12:54,542 --> 00:12:56,667
I always look like this, right?

183
00:12:56,667 --> 00:12:58,542
Oh, yeah, right.

184
00:12:58,542 --> 00:13:00,517
Okay, well, have a great time!

185
00:13:00,517 --> 00:13:02,000
PD Shin, I'll see you at the meeting.

186
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,000
Oh, sure.

187
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,771
I'll text you later.

188
00:13:05,771 --> 00:13:09,083
I texted her a pic of where we were earlier.

189
00:13:09,083 --> 00:13:10,694
I guess she spotted us on her way past.

190
00:13:10,694 --> 00:13:12,742
I see.

191
00:13:16,658 --> 00:13:18,743
One moment.

192
00:13:18,743 --> 00:13:20,917
Hey.

193
00:13:20,917 --> 00:13:22,000
Wait, you didn't have to...

194
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,458
I took care of the bill already.

195
00:13:23,458 --> 00:13:25,292
You really didn't need to.

196
00:13:25,292 --> 00:13:27,875
Hey, the matchmaker's allowed to buy, right?

197
00:13:27,875 --> 00:13:29,208
I'm the older one here.

198
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:30,958
<i>Yumi's only move right now</i>

199
00:13:30,958 --> 00:13:32,792
<i>is exactly that.</i>

200
00:13:32,792 --> 00:13:34,917
<i>The pretty girl</i>

201
00:13:34,917 --> 00:13:37,250
[The pretty girl]
<i>who buys you food.</i>

202
00:13:38,096 --> 00:13:40,723
Enjoy the rest of your date.

203
00:13:40,723 --> 00:13:42,325
But...

204
00:13:49,315 --> 00:13:51,025
She paid for our meal?

205
00:13:51,025 --> 00:13:53,277
Yeah.

206
00:13:53,277 --> 00:13:56,405
Maybe I shouldn't have sent that photo.
She was worried about us.

207
00:13:56,405 --> 00:13:59,242
I think she came on purpose to buy us food.

208
00:14:03,787 --> 00:14:06,825
Thank you for the meal.

209
00:14:09,877 --> 00:14:12,171
She's such a wonderful person.

210
00:14:12,171 --> 00:14:14,006
She's great to work with too, right?

211
00:14:14,006 --> 00:14:15,707
Yeah.

212
00:14:16,592 --> 00:14:19,000
Yeah, it was right to treat them.

213
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,514
Since I ran into them anyway,

214
00:14:21,514 --> 00:14:23,516
good move.

215
00:14:23,516 --> 00:14:25,726
Totally the right call.

216
00:14:25,726 --> 00:14:27,770
The pretty girl

217
00:14:27,770 --> 00:14:29,917
who buys you food?

218
00:14:29,917 --> 00:14:34,010
[The pretty girl who buys you food]

219
00:14:35,110 --> 00:14:39,031
Yumi's really just the generous noona now?

220
00:14:39,031 --> 00:14:41,292
There was no other way out of that.

221
00:14:41,292 --> 00:14:44,458
At least she played it off smoothly.

222
00:14:44,458 --> 00:14:46,997
I didn't wake up
for this noona-who-treats role.

223
00:14:46,997 --> 00:14:49,458
This is not what I came back for.

224
00:14:49,458 --> 00:14:53,170
Hey, at least she's the "pretty" noona.

225
00:14:53,170 --> 00:14:57,040
She could just be the noona who buys food.

226
00:15:08,060 --> 00:15:10,187
- Hi there.
- Oh, hello!

227
00:15:10,187 --> 00:15:12,250
Ten Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang,
please.

228
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:13,250
Sure.

229
00:15:13,250 --> 00:15:16,360
It'll be about a 5-minute wait though.

230
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:17,917
- No problem.
- Okay.

231
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:20,189
- I'll take care of the bill first.
- Okay.

232
00:15:21,490 --> 00:15:23,867
There you go, all done.

233
00:15:24,827 --> 00:15:26,662
By the way,

234
00:15:26,662 --> 00:15:28,872
are you feeling okay?

235
00:15:28,872 --> 00:15:30,082
Me?

236
00:15:30,082 --> 00:15:32,292
Oh, no, I'm fine.

237
00:15:32,292 --> 00:15:35,044
It's just that you seem kind of worn out.

238
00:15:36,750 --> 00:15:39,292
Is it that obvious?

239
00:15:39,292 --> 00:15:41,825
Work's been crazy busy these days.

240
00:15:42,542 --> 00:15:44,930
<i>I told you to put on makeup before leaving!</i>

241
00:15:44,930 --> 00:15:49,167
<i>"Worn out" is just a nice way of saying a mess.</i>

242
00:15:49,167 --> 00:15:54,469
[Bbang-eo Bbang-eo]

243
00:16:04,583 --> 00:16:07,286
<i>Thank you so much for the meal!</i>

244
00:16:07,286 --> 00:16:08,954
<i>I really appreciate it!</i>

245
00:16:08,954 --> 00:16:12,458
<i>Hot date plus a delicious meal.</i>

246
00:16:12,458 --> 00:16:14,533
<i>You're the best.</i>

247
00:16:17,253 --> 00:16:18,504
<i>As you get older,</i>

248
00:16:18,504 --> 00:16:22,700
<i>you need more and more reasons to save face.</i>

249
00:16:29,557 --> 00:16:33,102
<i>Maybe all those generous noonas out there</i>

250
00:16:33,102 --> 00:16:35,700
<i>might have the same reason.</i>

251
00:16:46,083 --> 00:16:48,870
[Episode 17: The Thrill of the Game]

252
00:16:59,378 --> 00:17:00,421
It's Jenny!

253
00:17:00,421 --> 00:17:02,798
Oh, it's Jenny.

254
00:17:02,798 --> 00:17:04,300
Is she really going to report back?

255
00:17:04,300 --> 00:17:05,667
Don't pick up.

256
00:17:05,667 --> 00:17:08,458
Let's finish writing first, then call back.

257
00:17:08,458 --> 00:17:10,950
How can we not answer?

258
00:17:18,526 --> 00:17:20,066
Hey, Jenny.

259
00:17:20,066 --> 00:17:22,276
<i>Are you at your studio?</i>

260
00:17:22,276 --> 00:17:24,362
Yeah, at the studio.

261
00:17:24,362 --> 00:17:26,113
Did it go...

262
00:17:26,113 --> 00:17:27,823
<i>I'm actually in the area.</i>

263
00:17:27,823 --> 00:17:30,542
<i>Mind if I stop by real quick?</i>

264
00:17:30,542 --> 00:17:31,542
Up here?

265
00:17:31,542 --> 00:17:33,246
<i>I have something for you.</i>

266
00:17:33,246 --> 00:17:35,667
Yeah, come on up.

267
00:17:35,667 --> 00:17:37,708
<i>Which unit was it again?</i>

268
00:17:37,708 --> 00:17:39,418
Room 1505.

269
00:17:39,418 --> 00:17:41,563
Okay, on my way!

270
00:17:50,346 --> 00:17:52,783
She's here already?

271
00:17:56,667 --> 00:17:57,728
Hey.

272
00:17:57,728 --> 00:18:00,333
Come on in.

273
00:18:00,333 --> 00:18:02,417
You've been really busy lately, right?

274
00:18:02,417 --> 00:18:05,987
PD Shin said you're super busy
before deadlines.

275
00:18:05,987 --> 00:18:07,656
Did she just say "PD Shin"?

276
00:18:07,656 --> 00:18:09,667
Wait, she's already calling him that?

277
00:18:09,667 --> 00:18:13,158
Better than "oppa," don't you think?

278
00:18:14,801 --> 00:18:16,208
It is hectic,

279
00:18:16,208 --> 00:18:20,292
but I've got a deadline every week,
so it's whatever.

280
00:18:20,292 --> 00:18:21,333
Actually,

281
00:18:21,333 --> 00:18:23,875
I came to give you this real quick.

282
00:18:23,875 --> 00:18:25,042
What is it?

283
00:18:25,042 --> 00:18:26,125
They're cookies!

284
00:18:26,125 --> 00:18:28,093
For a little pick-me-up when work gets tough.

285
00:18:28,093 --> 00:18:31,035
Oh come on, you shouldn't have!

286
00:18:31,035 --> 00:18:32,958
Have a seat. Want something to drink?

287
00:18:32,958 --> 00:18:34,000
Is that okay?

288
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,158
Yeah, totally.

289
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:41,606
I think this every time I visit,

290
00:18:41,606 --> 00:18:43,708
but this view is really something.

291
00:18:43,708 --> 00:18:44,750
Right?

292
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:47,492
The view is the only reason I'm still here.

293
00:18:48,395 --> 00:18:50,823
So, did it go well?

294
00:18:50,823 --> 00:18:52,908
The blind date?

295
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:57,292
How was it?

296
00:19:01,042 --> 00:19:04,250
Is it okay if I'm real with you?

297
00:19:04,250 --> 00:19:05,670
Guess it was a bust.

298
00:19:05,670 --> 00:19:06,796
Of course.

299
00:19:06,796 --> 00:19:08,542
What, he wasn't your type...

300
00:19:08,542 --> 00:19:10,583
I'm into him.

301
00:19:10,583 --> 00:19:12,825
She's into him?

302
00:19:16,473 --> 00:19:18,558
He's exactly what I'm looking for.

303
00:19:18,558 --> 00:19:19,750
Oh, really?

304
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:21,186
Yeah.

305
00:19:21,186 --> 00:19:26,066
His first impression was kind of distant,

306
00:19:26,066 --> 00:19:29,528
but when he smiled here and there,
it was adorable.

307
00:19:29,528 --> 00:19:32,280
Yeah, I know, I totally get that.

308
00:19:32,280 --> 00:19:34,583
Plus he's low-key hilarious.

309
00:19:34,583 --> 00:19:37,452
Kind of spacey in this endearing way?

310
00:19:37,452 --> 00:19:39,037
Yeah, I know what you mean.

311
00:19:39,037 --> 00:19:41,081
Believe me, I've seen it.

312
00:19:41,081 --> 00:19:43,542
Good to hear it went well.

313
00:19:43,542 --> 00:19:44,876
But the thing is,

314
00:19:44,876 --> 00:19:46,250
I'm not sure how PD Shin

315
00:19:46,250 --> 00:19:49,156
feels about me.

316
00:19:49,156 --> 00:19:50,167
How come?

317
00:19:50,167 --> 00:19:53,385
Things ended on a nice vibe,

318
00:19:53,385 --> 00:19:55,804
but something tells me he won't text first.

319
00:19:55,804 --> 00:19:57,264
I really can't tell.

320
00:19:57,264 --> 00:19:59,408
You make the first move then.

321
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,708
Yumi.

322
00:20:02,602 --> 00:20:05,750
Could you ask him for me?

323
00:20:05,750 --> 00:20:06,781
Me?

324
00:20:06,781 --> 00:20:07,816
Yeah.

325
00:20:07,816 --> 00:20:09,667
Just ask him what he thinks of me,

326
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:12,492
just casually?

327
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:15,500
Look,

328
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:17,743
we arranged the whole thing and bought lunch.

329
00:20:17,743 --> 00:20:20,042
Now we have to do follow-up support too?

330
00:20:20,042 --> 00:20:21,750
And whose fault is this?

331
00:20:21,750 --> 00:20:23,750
That generous noona bit,

332
00:20:23,750 --> 00:20:25,908
who came up with that?

333
00:20:29,805 --> 00:20:30,844
Alright, fine.

334
00:20:30,844 --> 00:20:32,000
I'll casually bring it up later...

335
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,042
Right now.

336
00:20:34,042 --> 00:20:37,033
Can you ask him right now?

337
00:20:38,008 --> 00:20:40,000
- Right now?
- Yes.

338
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:43,117
I seriously can't wait!

339
00:21:02,375 --> 00:21:04,000
[Writer Kim Yumi]

340
00:21:10,002 --> 00:21:11,378
Yes, it's me.

341
00:21:11,378 --> 00:21:13,964
<i>Is this a good time to talk?</i>

342
00:21:13,964 --> 00:21:15,340
Sure.

343
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:17,542
Oh, did you send the manuscript?

344
00:21:17,542 --> 00:21:19,450
I haven't checked my email yet...

345
00:21:19,450 --> 00:21:22,181
Oh, no, that's not why I'm calling.

346
00:21:22,181 --> 00:21:25,350
So how was it?

347
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:26,477
<i>Pardon?</i>

348
00:21:26,477 --> 00:21:28,992
The blind date today...

349
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:34,026
<i>I was just curious.</i>

350
00:21:34,026 --> 00:21:36,820
It went well, we had a good meeting.

351
00:21:36,820 --> 00:21:39,156
She was a great person.

352
00:21:39,156 --> 00:21:40,407
Isn't she though?

353
00:21:40,407 --> 00:21:42,208
Isn't Jenny adorable?

354
00:21:42,208 --> 00:21:44,375
She's so cheerful and fun to be around, right?

355
00:21:44,375 --> 00:21:47,167
She totally lights up the room.

356
00:21:47,167 --> 00:21:50,208
Yeah, that's the vibe I got.

357
00:21:51,335 --> 00:21:53,450
Right, so...

358
00:21:55,172 --> 00:21:56,965
Right, so...

359
00:21:56,965 --> 00:22:01,242
You'll meet up with her again, right?

360
00:22:03,583 --> 00:22:05,098
Yeah, sure.

361
00:22:05,098 --> 00:22:06,934
- You will?
- Yeah.

362
00:22:06,934 --> 00:22:08,769
I'll get in touch with her.

363
00:22:08,769 --> 00:22:10,312
Oh, right? I knew it.

364
00:22:10,312 --> 00:22:11,583
I'm glad to hear it.

365
00:22:11,583 --> 00:22:12,958
Alright then.

366
00:22:12,958 --> 00:22:16,360
I'll call you once I email the manuscript.

367
00:22:16,360 --> 00:22:18,158
Okay.

368
00:22:20,447 --> 00:22:22,407
PD Shin said

369
00:22:22,407 --> 00:22:24,868
he enjoyed it a lot, said it was really fun.

370
00:22:24,868 --> 00:22:26,912
For real?

371
00:22:26,912 --> 00:22:29,331
He'll probably text you any day now.

372
00:22:29,331 --> 00:22:31,500
I really appreciate this.

373
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:34,242
I was seriously so lonely.

374
00:22:36,208 --> 00:22:38,882
Trust me, I'm even more lonely.

375
00:22:38,882 --> 00:22:41,033
- What?
- Forget it.

376
00:22:45,597 --> 00:22:47,367
Wait a minute.

377
00:22:49,393 --> 00:22:51,700
This is kind of weird, isn't it?

378
00:22:58,234 --> 00:22:59,250
Hello?

379
00:22:59,250 --> 00:23:02,083
Love Cell, doesn't this feel weird?

380
00:23:02,083 --> 00:23:04,250
Could you have gotten this one wrong?

381
00:23:04,250 --> 00:23:07,667
Writer Kim seems to have
zero romantic interest in him.

382
00:23:07,667 --> 00:23:10,208
Excuse me, has my read ever been off?

383
00:23:10,208 --> 00:23:12,542
I'm literally an expert in this field.

384
00:23:12,542 --> 00:23:15,375
She arranged the date immediately,

385
00:23:15,375 --> 00:23:16,625
bought them lunch,

386
00:23:16,625 --> 00:23:18,708
and even made that phone call to help out.

387
00:23:18,708 --> 00:23:20,590
Was it wrong to set that boundary?

388
00:23:20,590 --> 00:23:22,292
<i>No, it wasn't pointless.</i>

389
00:23:22,292 --> 00:23:24,792
She lost interest because he drew the line.

390
00:23:24,792 --> 00:23:26,387
<i>You think that's what it is?</i>

391
00:23:26,387 --> 00:23:28,264
Anyway, isn't this a good thing?

392
00:23:28,264 --> 00:23:31,667
They're coworkers, so it's better this way.

393
00:23:31,667 --> 00:23:34,143
Sure, it's fine, but...

394
00:23:35,355 --> 00:23:37,658
Are we sure this is a good thing?

395
00:23:40,485 --> 00:23:43,475
<i>So why does it feel crummy?</i>

396
00:23:43,475 --> 00:23:44,864
<i>Me?</i>

397
00:23:44,864 --> 00:23:47,033
<i>I'm not in a bad mood.</i>

398
00:23:47,033 --> 00:23:49,285
<i>Right? You're fine, right?</i>

399
00:23:49,285 --> 00:23:50,500
<i>I'm just tired.</i>

400
00:23:50,500 --> 00:23:53,825
<i>Right, it's just because you're tired.</i>

401
00:24:00,917 --> 00:24:03,417
[Love Cell]

402
00:24:27,125 --> 00:24:28,833
Hello.

403
00:24:28,833 --> 00:24:30,292
Oh, you're here?

404
00:24:30,292 --> 00:24:33,125
I figured you'd come with PD Jang.

405
00:24:33,125 --> 00:24:35,708
I stopped by a different meeting first.

406
00:24:35,708 --> 00:24:38,609
Okay. Can I get you some coffee?

407
00:24:38,609 --> 00:24:40,429
An iced Americano, if you have one?

408
00:24:40,429 --> 00:24:41,458
Sure thing.

409
00:24:41,458 --> 00:24:42,875
Thanks.

410
00:24:48,051 --> 00:24:50,471
I really enjoyed the script.

411
00:24:50,471 --> 00:24:51,958
Oh, really?

412
00:24:51,958 --> 00:24:54,042
Yeah, especially this episode,

413
00:24:54,042 --> 00:24:57,060
the emotional scenes were so good.

414
00:24:57,060 --> 00:24:59,313
Oh, what a relief.

415
00:24:59,313 --> 00:25:03,025
When you say it's good, it's really good,

416
00:25:03,025 --> 00:25:06,283
because you can't say nice things
just to be polite.

417
00:25:07,833 --> 00:25:10,458
Is that really how I come across?

418
00:25:10,458 --> 00:25:12,159
It's not an image.

419
00:25:12,159 --> 00:25:15,496
That's just who you are.

420
00:25:15,496 --> 00:25:17,498
Oh, I see.

421
00:25:17,498 --> 00:25:19,783
So that's who I am.

422
00:25:20,750 --> 00:25:22,336
There are some small things,

423
00:25:22,336 --> 00:25:25,088
I'll go over them during the meeting.

424
00:25:25,088 --> 00:25:26,825
Okay.

425
00:25:35,531 --> 00:25:36,850
<i>Yumi.</i>

426
00:25:36,850 --> 00:25:38,769
<i>Your meeting is today, right?</i>

427
00:25:38,769 --> 00:25:40,771
<i>Did PD Shin show up?</i>

428
00:25:40,771 --> 00:25:42,731
<i>I'm just curious.</i>

429
00:25:42,731 --> 00:25:45,533
<i>I still haven't heard from him.</i>

430
00:25:48,854 --> 00:25:50,567
By the way...

431
00:25:52,333 --> 00:25:54,825
Did you contact her?

432
00:25:56,912 --> 00:25:58,992
Jenny, I mean.

433
00:26:01,458 --> 00:26:03,333
Not yet.

434
00:26:04,708 --> 00:26:06,283
I see.

435
00:26:14,471 --> 00:26:16,764
Is that something

436
00:26:16,764 --> 00:26:18,783
I have to do?

437
00:26:20,560 --> 00:26:22,292
No.

438
00:26:22,292 --> 00:26:25,273
That's not what I meant, obviously.

439
00:26:25,273 --> 00:26:26,524
Yeah.

440
00:26:26,524 --> 00:26:28,783
I'll reach out to her soon.

441
00:26:30,250 --> 00:26:31,458
<i>What was that?</i>

442
00:26:31,458 --> 00:26:33,072
<i>Why did his face look so cold?</i>

443
00:26:33,072 --> 00:26:34,323
<i>Don't read into it.</i>

444
00:26:34,323 --> 00:26:36,658
<i>He looked the same as always.</i>

445
00:27:15,750 --> 00:27:17,917
- I'm here!
- Oh, hey, you're here?

446
00:27:17,917 --> 00:27:19,820
You guys showed up at the same time?

447
00:27:19,820 --> 00:27:22,917
- Hello.
- We bumped into each other on the way in.

448
00:27:22,917 --> 00:27:24,457
Hi, PD Shin.

449
00:27:24,457 --> 00:27:25,833
PD Shin, you beat us here?

450
00:27:25,833 --> 00:27:27,658
Hello.

451
00:28:05,708 --> 00:28:07,208
[Jenny]

452
00:28:07,208 --> 00:28:09,992
<i>PD Shin texted me!</i>

453
00:28:10,750 --> 00:28:13,992
<i>We made plans for Friday!</i>

454
00:28:15,208 --> 00:28:17,500
<i>Good for you.</i>

455
00:28:17,500 --> 00:28:20,117
<i>I'll make it work! Wish me luck!</i>

456
00:28:24,732 --> 00:28:25,768
<i>Alright.</i>

457
00:28:25,768 --> 00:28:27,333
<i>I feel better now, honestly.</i>

458
00:28:27,333 --> 00:28:28,980
<i>We did our part.</i>

459
00:28:28,980 --> 00:28:30,523
<i>Time to let it go.</i>

460
00:28:30,523 --> 00:28:32,441
You two figure it out yourselves.

461
00:28:32,441 --> 00:28:34,617
Please, just leave me out of it.

462
00:28:59,458 --> 00:29:01,617
What should I make?

463
00:29:53,292 --> 00:29:57,408
<i>It's going over the wall, over the fence!</i>

464
00:30:17,503 --> 00:30:20,200
<i>This is weird though.</i>

465
00:30:31,976 --> 00:30:34,312
- Heave-ho, heave-ho!
- Heave-ho, heave-ho!

466
00:30:34,312 --> 00:30:37,000
- Heave-ho, heave-ho!
- This is strange.

467
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:41,121
- He's home, so why can't he recharge?
- Heave-ho, heave-ho!

468
00:30:47,074 --> 00:30:49,450
Let me sleep some more.

469
00:30:54,120 --> 00:30:55,125
Hello?

470
00:30:55,125 --> 00:30:57,792
[Love Cell]
<i>Hey! You messed things up for nothing.</i>

471
00:30:58,705 --> 00:31:00,880
That stupid removal surgery or whatever,

472
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:03,167
bringing up the blind date for no reason,

473
00:31:03,167 --> 00:31:06,458
he drew the line to avoid relationship drama,

474
00:31:06,458 --> 00:31:08,429
and now things are even more complicated.

475
00:31:08,429 --> 00:31:10,417
He came home and he's not recovering at all.

476
00:31:10,417 --> 00:31:13,292
His head is too full of thoughts.

477
00:31:13,292 --> 00:31:15,292
Look, when you're that beat,

478
00:31:15,292 --> 00:31:17,167
- recharging takes longer.
<i>- Wrong!</i>

479
00:31:17,167 --> 00:31:18,875
<i>It's because the surgery went wrong.</i>

480
00:31:18,875 --> 00:31:21,908
So what are you going to do now?

481
00:31:35,542 --> 00:31:37,867
[Writer Baek Na Hui]

482
00:31:44,542 --> 00:31:46,133
Hello?

483
00:31:46,133 --> 00:31:48,594
<i>Are you free to talk?</i>

484
00:31:48,594 --> 00:31:49,679
Yeah.

485
00:31:49,679 --> 00:31:52,515
So, for the male lead's gaming storyline,

486
00:31:52,515 --> 00:31:55,977
Writer Kim ordered a console to try it herself.

487
00:31:55,977 --> 00:31:57,770
It arrived a little while ago.

488
00:31:57,770 --> 00:31:59,492
<i>Oh, it did?</i>

489
00:31:59,492 --> 00:32:01,417
I figured it'd be no big deal to install,

490
00:32:01,417 --> 00:32:03,125
so I said I'd handle it, but...

491
00:32:03,125 --> 00:32:05,403
I'm completely lost.

492
00:32:05,403 --> 00:32:08,208
Didn't you say you have that same console?

493
00:32:08,208 --> 00:32:09,949
That's right.

494
00:32:09,949 --> 00:32:13,375
Don't worry about it.
I'll install it on my next visit.

495
00:32:13,375 --> 00:32:16,330
Okay, I'm throwing in the towel and leaving.

496
00:32:16,330 --> 00:32:18,250
I'll tuck it away in the corner.

497
00:32:18,250 --> 00:32:20,959
Wouldn't Writer Kim

498
00:32:20,959 --> 00:32:23,000
want to try it out as soon as possible?

499
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:24,125
Yeah, good point,

500
00:32:24,125 --> 00:32:26,500
but your visit is Friday, so until then...

501
00:32:26,500 --> 00:32:28,383
- What if I head over right now?
<i>- Excuse me?</i>

502
00:32:28,383 --> 00:32:30,886
Leave everything and text me the passcode.

503
00:32:30,886 --> 00:32:33,408
I'll swing by and get it all hooked up.

504
00:32:34,882 --> 00:32:36,061
Isn't it kind of late though?

505
00:32:36,061 --> 00:32:38,935
It's not like I have anything else to do.

506
00:32:38,935 --> 00:32:41,605
He's heading out again after coming home?

507
00:32:41,605 --> 00:32:43,958
It's not like he's recovering at home.

508
00:32:43,958 --> 00:32:46,533
I still don't know why.

509
00:33:05,712 --> 00:33:10,258
Might as well burn off energy and pass out.

510
00:33:10,258 --> 00:33:13,117
<i>Beginning route navigation.</i>

511
00:34:07,583 --> 00:34:09,637
[Setting up internet connection]

512
00:34:18,577 --> 00:34:20,325
Done.

513
00:34:32,882 --> 00:34:34,783
Writer Kim.

514
00:34:36,010 --> 00:34:37,553
Wait, what's going on?

515
00:34:37,553 --> 00:34:39,930
Why is Writer Kim suddenly here?

516
00:34:39,930 --> 00:34:42,433
This is bad, we're almost blacking out.

517
00:34:42,433 --> 00:34:45,667
Hold it together, man.

518
00:34:45,667 --> 00:34:47,164
Hold tight!

519
00:34:48,439 --> 00:34:50,783
- Why are you here so late...
- Why are you here so late...

520
00:34:52,276 --> 00:34:54,195
I'm just here to install this thing.

521
00:34:54,195 --> 00:34:57,158
Na Hui called and said she was stuck.

522
00:34:57,781 --> 00:35:00,701
That really could have waited, you know.

523
00:35:00,701 --> 00:35:02,953
I didn't have anything better to do.

524
00:35:02,953 --> 00:35:05,289
But what brings you here...

525
00:35:05,289 --> 00:35:07,407
Oh, me?

526
00:35:09,251 --> 00:35:11,462
I couldn't sleep,

527
00:35:11,462 --> 00:35:15,883
so I figured I'd get a head start
on episode 16.

528
00:35:15,883 --> 00:35:18,835
You really scared me though.

529
00:35:19,792 --> 00:35:21,667
It's nearly finished, just ten more minutes...

530
00:35:21,667 --> 00:35:23,015
Don't worry about it, just do your thing.

531
00:35:23,015 --> 00:35:25,059
The writing can wait.

532
00:35:25,059 --> 00:35:27,033
It'll just take a second.

533
00:35:39,114 --> 00:35:42,875
I brought Strawberry Cream Custard Bungeoppang.

534
00:35:42,875 --> 00:35:44,453
Want some?

535
00:35:44,453 --> 00:35:46,955
Yes, I'd love some.

536
00:35:46,955 --> 00:35:48,206
What about a drink?

537
00:35:48,206 --> 00:35:50,333
Milk, or...

538
00:35:50,333 --> 00:35:52,210
there's Coke too.

539
00:35:52,210 --> 00:35:54,125
I'll have milk.

540
00:35:54,125 --> 00:35:55,130
Good choice.

541
00:35:55,130 --> 00:35:57,883
Of course, milk goes with strawberry cream.

542
00:35:57,883 --> 00:36:01,450
When you mentioned Coke, I was thrown off.

543
00:36:08,685 --> 00:36:10,625
Here you go.

544
00:36:10,625 --> 00:36:12,564
Thank you.

545
00:36:12,564 --> 00:36:13,607
So...

546
00:36:13,607 --> 00:36:16,401
why don't you have a seat?

547
00:36:16,401 --> 00:36:18,117
Me?

548
00:36:18,904 --> 00:36:21,364
Have you played on one of these before?

549
00:36:21,364 --> 00:36:24,826
No, I'm absolutely terrible at gaming.

550
00:36:24,826 --> 00:36:26,453
I'll give you a quick rundown.

551
00:36:26,453 --> 00:36:28,788
Have a seat.

552
00:36:28,788 --> 00:36:31,617
Sure.

553
00:36:34,169 --> 00:36:36,481
You do everything through this controller.

554
00:36:36,481 --> 00:36:39,049
Oh yeah, I've seen these around.

555
00:36:39,049 --> 00:36:41,593
It might take a couple days to get used to it.

556
00:36:41,593 --> 00:36:43,094
First, put your hands

557
00:36:43,094 --> 00:36:46,139
like this, just like this.

558
00:36:46,139 --> 00:36:47,849
Thumbs up here like this.

559
00:36:47,849 --> 00:36:50,079
Yes, just like that.

560
00:36:51,167 --> 00:36:52,292
Okay, and over here,

561
00:36:52,292 --> 00:36:55,106
- see the X and O?
- Yeah.

562
00:36:55,106 --> 00:36:56,441
O is for going back,

563
00:36:56,441 --> 00:36:58,286
and X is the start button.

564
00:36:59,486 --> 00:37:01,771
Want to give it a try?

565
00:37:02,500 --> 00:37:04,000
Start.

566
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:05,075
No, not that.

567
00:37:05,075 --> 00:37:07,458
- Hit the X button.
- Ah, okay, X, got it.

568
00:37:07,458 --> 00:37:08,458
There you go.

569
00:37:08,458 --> 00:37:09,965
[Character Select]

570
00:37:13,500 --> 00:37:16,208
Look, here we go, right?

571
00:37:16,208 --> 00:37:17,754
So this is how it starts.

572
00:37:17,754 --> 00:37:21,758
Good. Now let's try moving and jumping.

573
00:37:21,758 --> 00:37:24,135
Left hand pushes the stick forward,

574
00:37:24,135 --> 00:37:26,638
right hand hits X twice,

575
00:37:26,638 --> 00:37:28,223
then tap square once fast.

576
00:37:28,223 --> 00:37:29,966
Give it a shot?

577
00:37:31,100 --> 00:37:32,976
Wait, not like that.

578
00:37:32,976 --> 00:37:34,520
Wait, no, shoot.

579
00:37:34,520 --> 00:37:35,979
See, this way.

580
00:37:35,979 --> 00:37:38,950
Right, so I do this, and...

581
00:37:39,958 --> 00:37:42,408
No, not that either.

582
00:37:43,153 --> 00:37:45,531
One second.

583
00:37:45,531 --> 00:37:48,492
Left stick forward,

584
00:37:48,492 --> 00:37:51,319
right hand X twice.

585
00:37:54,623 --> 00:37:56,875
Then square, and that makes it

586
00:37:56,875 --> 00:37:58,908
go like this, right?

587
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:01,700
You see that?

588
00:38:02,542 --> 00:38:05,200
You get how the controls work now?

589
00:38:19,982 --> 00:38:22,809
You see the idea behind it, right?

590
00:38:23,569 --> 00:38:25,946
I understand the concept,

591
00:38:25,946 --> 00:38:29,241
but I need some hands-on practice.

592
00:38:29,241 --> 00:38:30,325
Right.

593
00:38:30,325 --> 00:38:32,786
You'll need a couple days to get comfortable.

594
00:38:32,786 --> 00:38:34,705
Yeah, let me mess around with it by myself.

595
00:38:34,705 --> 00:38:36,408
Alright.

596
00:38:46,667 --> 00:38:47,843
Wait, does it...

597
00:38:47,843 --> 00:38:48,969
No? Wrong again?

598
00:38:48,969 --> 00:38:51,096
- What's going on?
- Easy, go slow.

599
00:38:51,096 --> 00:38:54,200
Right, slow...

600
00:38:56,518 --> 00:38:57,769
It worked!

601
00:38:57,769 --> 00:38:59,637
Or not?

602
00:39:02,524 --> 00:39:05,277
- What's wrong now?
- No, go forward at the same time.

603
00:39:05,277 --> 00:39:07,571
This way?

604
00:39:07,571 --> 00:39:09,408
Hold on.

605
00:39:19,041 --> 00:39:21,200
I did it!

606
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:50,113
Just like that.

607
00:39:50,113 --> 00:39:51,792
Oh, okay!

608
00:39:51,792 --> 00:39:54,159
Yeah, I totally get it now.

609
00:39:54,159 --> 00:39:57,621
How do I... let me just do it myself this time.

610
00:39:57,621 --> 00:39:59,408
Oh, sure.

611
00:40:12,167 --> 00:40:13,958
I did it.

612
00:40:15,264 --> 00:40:16,890
Oh, it's actually simple.

613
00:40:16,890 --> 00:40:18,716
You're pretty good at this.

614
00:40:19,393 --> 00:40:21,013
How about trying a different game?

615
00:40:21,013 --> 00:40:22,042
Oh, right now?

616
00:40:22,042 --> 00:40:23,042
Yeah.

617
00:40:23,042 --> 00:40:24,458
Which ones are fun?

618
00:40:24,458 --> 00:40:26,283
Give me a second.

619
00:40:32,730 --> 00:40:33,972
Oh, this one's really fun.

620
00:40:33,972 --> 00:40:35,707
It's super popular right now.

621
00:40:35,707 --> 00:40:38,750
Absolute beginners can do this one. Trust me.

622
00:40:38,750 --> 00:40:40,250
Plus,

623
00:40:40,250 --> 00:40:42,042
oh, this, this right here

624
00:40:42,042 --> 00:40:45,250
is story-driven. You would love this.

625
00:40:45,250 --> 00:40:47,796
It's really worth trying, this one...

626
00:40:47,796 --> 00:40:50,000
By the way...

627
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:53,242
Don't you need to head out? It's so late.

628
00:40:54,417 --> 00:40:57,125
It's past 12 already.

629
00:40:57,833 --> 00:41:00,158
Oh, wait...

630
00:41:01,042 --> 00:41:03,783
You're right.

631
00:41:05,040 --> 00:41:06,792
I'll figure it out by myself.

632
00:41:06,792 --> 00:41:09,125
I'm sure I'll learn as I play.

633
00:41:09,125 --> 00:41:12,490
Sure, no rush, just play around.

634
00:41:12,490 --> 00:41:14,323
I appreciate you doing this so late at night.

635
00:41:14,323 --> 00:41:16,292
It was nothing.

636
00:41:16,292 --> 00:41:18,749
Alright, I'll head out now.

637
00:41:18,749 --> 00:41:20,250
Sure.

638
00:41:20,250 --> 00:41:21,750
I'll just tidy this up before I go...

639
00:41:21,750 --> 00:41:24,458
Oh, leave that, I'll clean it up myself!

640
00:41:24,458 --> 00:41:27,367
I'll just toss the box on my way down.

641
00:41:39,972 --> 00:41:41,432
Thank you.

642
00:41:41,432 --> 00:41:42,772
No problem.

643
00:41:42,772 --> 00:41:46,228
If you get stuck, just call me anytime.

644
00:41:46,228 --> 00:41:48,689
I should try it myself. I won't bother you.

645
00:41:48,689 --> 00:41:50,742
It wouldn't be a bother.

646
00:41:51,990 --> 00:41:53,027
Oh, okay then.

647
00:41:53,027 --> 00:41:55,946
If I really can't figure it out, I'll call.

648
00:41:55,946 --> 00:41:57,658
Okay.

649
00:42:06,290 --> 00:42:08,667
- Get home safe.
<i>- Going down.</i>

650
00:42:08,667 --> 00:42:09,793
Good night.

651
00:42:09,793 --> 00:42:12,283
<i>Doors are closing.</i>

652
00:42:27,269 --> 00:42:29,161
It's so late.

653
00:42:31,190 --> 00:42:32,708
He was already tired enough,

654
00:42:32,708 --> 00:42:35,575
and he didn't even recharge at all...

655
00:42:41,283 --> 00:42:42,833
What is this?

656
00:42:42,833 --> 00:42:46,283
He's not even home,
so why is everything lit up?

657
00:43:36,708 --> 00:43:41,591
[Episode 18: Vintage Wine]

658
00:43:44,846 --> 00:43:46,533
Where are you off to?

659
00:43:47,265 --> 00:43:48,933
I'm going to a meeting.

660
00:43:48,933 --> 00:43:51,436
- Writer Kim's team meeting?
- Yeah.

661
00:43:51,436 --> 00:43:53,730
- What's up?
- When do you think you'll wrap up?

662
00:43:53,730 --> 00:43:55,023
Not sure.

663
00:43:55,023 --> 00:43:56,191
About two or three hours?

664
00:43:56,191 --> 00:43:57,333
Having dinner there too?

665
00:43:57,333 --> 00:43:59,279
I'll most likely be done before dinner.

666
00:43:59,279 --> 00:44:00,320
What's this about...

667
00:44:00,320 --> 00:44:02,030
Nothing. Good luck in there.

668
00:44:02,030 --> 00:44:03,742
Have a good one!

669
00:44:18,708 --> 00:44:21,674
<i>PD Shin, do you have a second?</i>

670
00:44:21,674 --> 00:44:24,552
<i>Where should we meet up tonight?</i>

671
00:44:24,552 --> 00:44:27,639
Oh shoot! He totally forgot to book a table!

672
00:44:27,639 --> 00:44:30,492
He said he would handle it.

673
00:44:31,833 --> 00:44:35,075
[Best places to eat in Gwanghwamun]

674
00:44:36,189 --> 00:44:38,024
Friday night, of all nights.

675
00:44:38,024 --> 00:44:40,742
There might not be any tables left.

676
00:44:41,903 --> 00:44:44,117
I'll get going now.

677
00:44:46,699 --> 00:44:48,243
I'm heading out.

678
00:44:48,243 --> 00:44:50,408
Alright, take care.

679
00:44:52,163 --> 00:44:54,666
How about switching the username?

680
00:44:54,666 --> 00:44:57,252
The ID is what gives it away.

681
00:44:57,252 --> 00:45:00,213
Does that actually fix the plot hole though?

682
00:45:00,213 --> 00:45:03,091
The audience probably won't catch that.

683
00:45:03,091 --> 00:45:06,427
What if we say they switched
security companies?

684
00:45:06,427 --> 00:45:08,096
The security company?

685
00:45:08,096 --> 00:45:11,542
If they switch companies,
everything changes anyway.

686
00:45:11,542 --> 00:45:14,292
And the lead was traveling, so he had no idea.

687
00:45:14,292 --> 00:45:16,354
That's actually a solid idea.

688
00:45:16,354 --> 00:45:18,649
But if you switch security companies,

689
00:45:18,649 --> 00:45:20,858
I don't know what all would change...

690
00:45:20,858 --> 00:45:22,318
Let me research that.

691
00:45:22,318 --> 00:45:23,500
I can check on that for you.

692
00:45:23,500 --> 00:45:25,625
A buddy of mine works in security.

693
00:45:25,625 --> 00:45:28,157
Yes please, I'm clueless on that stuff.

694
00:45:28,157 --> 00:45:29,576
I'll get on it.

695
00:45:29,576 --> 00:45:31,744
Thank you.

696
00:45:31,744 --> 00:45:34,539
Okay, looks like we're all wrapped up.

697
00:45:34,539 --> 00:45:36,542
Let's wrap up the meeting here?

698
00:45:36,542 --> 00:45:38,042
Yes, good job today.

699
00:45:38,042 --> 00:45:39,083
Yeah.

700
00:45:39,083 --> 00:45:40,667
So what about dinner?

701
00:45:40,667 --> 00:45:42,042
Let's grab something light and head out?

702
00:45:42,042 --> 00:45:43,292
Sure, works for me.

703
00:45:43,292 --> 00:45:46,175
I've got somewhere to be, sorry.

704
00:45:46,175 --> 00:45:48,875
Oh right, you have a thing.

705
00:45:48,875 --> 00:45:50,042
Okay, we'll grab dinner ourselves.

706
00:45:50,042 --> 00:45:51,973
Sure!

707
00:45:51,973 --> 00:45:54,292
Where are you off to, PD Shin?

708
00:45:54,292 --> 00:45:56,325
Good work today.

709
00:46:17,500 --> 00:46:20,750
<i>Two dates is enough to be polite.</i>

710
00:46:20,750 --> 00:46:23,075
<i>Let's wrap things up with her today.</i>

711
00:46:38,792 --> 00:46:40,167
Hey, I'm here now.

712
00:46:40,167 --> 00:46:41,250
What floor is it?

713
00:46:41,250 --> 00:46:43,700
15th? Okay, got it.

714
00:46:45,542 --> 00:46:48,104
<i>Wait, isn't that Writer Kim Ju Ho?</i>

715
00:46:48,104 --> 00:46:50,049
<i>Why is he here?</i>

716
00:46:52,042 --> 00:46:54,658
Well, meetings always wrap up quick.

717
00:47:06,875 --> 00:47:08,667
Who is it?

718
00:47:08,667 --> 00:47:10,250
Who is it?

719
00:47:10,250 --> 00:47:12,456
<i>Oh, hi, I'm writer Kim Ju Ho.</i>

720
00:47:12,456 --> 00:47:13,500
Writer Kim.

721
00:47:13,500 --> 00:47:14,500
Who is it?

722
00:47:14,500 --> 00:47:16,473
He says he's Writer Kim Ju Ho.

723
00:47:16,473 --> 00:47:17,692
Kim Ju Ho?

724
00:47:17,692 --> 00:47:19,225
Yes.

725
00:47:19,225 --> 00:47:20,375
He came all the way here?

726
00:47:20,375 --> 00:47:22,145
Yeah, what should I do?

727
00:47:22,145 --> 00:47:24,647
Wait, what?

728
00:47:24,647 --> 00:47:27,250
Just let him in for now.

729
00:47:27,250 --> 00:47:28,250
Hello.

730
00:47:28,250 --> 00:47:29,569
- Oh, yes.
- Please come in.

731
00:47:29,569 --> 00:47:32,417
He's here.

732
00:47:32,417 --> 00:47:34,708
Oh, hello.

733
00:47:34,708 --> 00:47:37,076
Hello.

734
00:47:37,076 --> 00:47:39,287
Sorry, did I come at a bad time?

735
00:47:39,287 --> 00:47:41,000
Mind if I stop in for a second?

736
00:47:41,000 --> 00:47:42,500
Sure, please, have a seat.

737
00:47:42,500 --> 00:47:44,325
Thanks.

738
00:47:47,875 --> 00:47:50,407
This studio is seriously nice.

739
00:47:50,407 --> 00:47:54,458
This place is so you.

740
00:47:54,458 --> 00:47:57,514
Sorry, I must have caught you off guard.

741
00:47:57,514 --> 00:47:59,208
Of course I am.

742
00:47:59,208 --> 00:48:02,792
Showing up out of nowhere with no heads up...

743
00:48:02,792 --> 00:48:06,147
I had something to do in Ilsan,

744
00:48:06,147 --> 00:48:08,982
and I recalled your studio was in this area.

745
00:48:08,982 --> 00:48:10,833
So I checked with Dae Yong,

746
00:48:10,833 --> 00:48:14,000
he mentioned your meeting today
so I thought you'd be in.

747
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:16,375
Oh, I see.

748
00:48:16,375 --> 00:48:17,866
And...

749
00:48:17,866 --> 00:48:20,458
I wanted to give you this.

750
00:48:20,458 --> 00:48:23,408
Oh, it's wine.

751
00:48:24,042 --> 00:48:26,792
I just got back from a quick trip to Europe.

752
00:48:26,792 --> 00:48:29,000
I picked up a few bottles of vintage wine,

753
00:48:29,000 --> 00:48:32,422
and you came to mind.

754
00:48:32,422 --> 00:48:34,575
Thank you.

755
00:48:35,417 --> 00:48:38,542
Do you like vintage wine by any chance?

756
00:48:38,542 --> 00:48:41,570
I don't really know much about wine.

757
00:48:42,333 --> 00:48:46,057
That one's from 1997.

758
00:48:46,895 --> 00:48:49,833
From 1997?

759
00:48:49,833 --> 00:48:51,817
I have a feeling

760
00:48:51,817 --> 00:48:54,417
you weren't even alive back then, am I right?

761
00:48:54,417 --> 00:48:57,583
That's right, I'm a '99 baby.

762
00:48:57,583 --> 00:48:59,658
Do you recall?

763
00:48:59,658 --> 00:49:01,083
Back in '97, we...

764
00:49:01,083 --> 00:49:02,994
I honestly cannot remember

765
00:49:02,994 --> 00:49:05,414
a thing about 1997.

766
00:49:05,414 --> 00:49:07,000
I was just a little kid.

767
00:49:07,000 --> 00:49:08,958
I'm not from your era,

768
00:49:08,958 --> 00:49:10,742
so don't go there.

769
00:49:12,671 --> 00:49:14,005
Anyway,

770
00:49:14,005 --> 00:49:17,117
this seems way too fancy. Why me?

771
00:49:18,552 --> 00:49:21,054
Think of it as a make-up bribe.

772
00:49:21,054 --> 00:49:23,849
I was pretty rude back in Busan,

773
00:49:23,849 --> 00:49:26,375
so I wanted to make it right.

774
00:49:26,375 --> 00:49:28,228
Oh, well...

775
00:49:28,228 --> 00:49:30,667
When you say it like that,

776
00:49:30,667 --> 00:49:33,741
then I should be sorry as well.

777
00:49:33,741 --> 00:49:36,736
I got way too heated that day myself...

778
00:49:36,736 --> 00:49:40,073
So does that make us square?

779
00:49:40,073 --> 00:49:41,625
Well,

780
00:49:41,625 --> 00:49:43,243
there's nothing to keep score over.

781
00:49:43,243 --> 00:49:45,495
Let's just call it a misunderstanding.

782
00:49:45,495 --> 00:49:47,080
Yeah, totally!

783
00:49:47,080 --> 00:49:49,878
Man, you're such a good sport.

784
00:49:49,878 --> 00:49:51,208
Dae Yong wouldn't stop telling me

785
00:49:51,208 --> 00:49:54,750
to come here and make things right.

786
00:49:54,750 --> 00:49:56,381
So you were dragged here.

787
00:49:56,381 --> 00:49:58,258
That explains it...

788
00:49:58,258 --> 00:50:01,219
Anyway, let's just

789
00:50:01,219 --> 00:50:03,263
shake on it, at least.

790
00:50:03,263 --> 00:50:05,417
I'm sorry.

791
00:50:05,417 --> 00:50:06,458
Well, I'm not sure

792
00:50:06,458 --> 00:50:08,810
this needs to be this official, but...

793
00:50:08,810 --> 00:50:10,492
okay.

794
00:50:12,292 --> 00:50:14,834
Do we need a selfie for evidence too?

795
00:50:14,834 --> 00:50:16,908
For the editor's peace of mind.

796
00:50:17,903 --> 00:50:21,531
See, this is why you're the best.

797
00:50:21,531 --> 00:50:22,629
Sit down, please.

798
00:50:22,629 --> 00:50:23,643
Okay.

799
00:50:24,284 --> 00:50:26,745
Want some coffee?

800
00:50:26,745 --> 00:50:29,456
Oh, you're offering coffee too?

801
00:50:29,456 --> 00:50:30,875
Of course, what would you like?

802
00:50:30,875 --> 00:50:32,750
Well, then...

803
00:50:32,750 --> 00:50:35,917
an iced latte, please.

804
00:50:35,917 --> 00:50:37,825
One moment.

805
00:50:45,680 --> 00:50:47,807
Oh, but I don't see PD Shin around.

806
00:50:47,807 --> 00:50:49,875
I assumed he'd be at the meeting too.

807
00:50:49,875 --> 00:50:52,604
He had somewhere to be, so he took off.

808
00:50:52,604 --> 00:50:55,607
Did he catch wind of my visit and bail?

809
00:50:55,607 --> 00:50:57,609
I don't think so.

810
00:50:57,609 --> 00:50:59,486
He's got a bone to pick with me.

811
00:50:59,486 --> 00:51:02,906
I heard you were the one who was salty.

812
00:51:02,906 --> 00:51:04,157
Excuse me?

813
00:51:04,157 --> 00:51:06,359
Please, that's not true at all.

814
00:51:10,276 --> 00:51:11,831
But, with him not here,

815
00:51:11,831 --> 00:51:13,667
it's actually more relaxed.

816
00:51:13,667 --> 00:51:16,410
He acts like your bodyguard all the time.

817
00:51:18,833 --> 00:51:20,820
Excuse me?

818
00:51:20,820 --> 00:51:22,801
Your meeting is over, right?

819
00:51:22,801 --> 00:51:25,408
Want to grab dinner with me?

820
00:51:36,856 --> 00:51:39,283
<i>I'm here now.</i>

821
00:51:40,960 --> 00:51:43,075
<i>I'm almost there too.</i>

822
00:51:55,124 --> 00:51:56,458
Yes, PD Shin.

823
00:51:56,458 --> 00:51:57,460
<i>It's me.</i>

824
00:51:57,460 --> 00:51:59,003
Still at the studio?

825
00:51:59,003 --> 00:52:01,575
No, I'm out now.

826
00:52:02,214 --> 00:52:03,674
Nothing wrong, right?

827
00:52:03,674 --> 00:52:05,492
<i>What do you mean?</i>

828
00:52:06,469 --> 00:52:08,512
Did Writer Kim Ju Ho

829
00:52:08,512 --> 00:52:09,555
take off?

830
00:52:09,555 --> 00:52:12,833
How did you know he was here?

831
00:52:12,833 --> 00:52:14,226
I spotted him when I was leaving.

832
00:52:14,226 --> 00:52:18,492
We're having dinner with him right now.

833
00:52:19,189 --> 00:52:20,274
Dinner?

834
00:52:20,274 --> 00:52:23,694
Yeah, he brought vintage wine,

835
00:52:23,694 --> 00:52:26,530
and he said let's open it,
so we came to Luche Vino.

836
00:52:26,530 --> 00:52:28,542
<i>It's so good, by the way.</i>

837
00:52:28,542 --> 00:52:32,453
<i>And he knows so much about wine too.</i>

838
00:52:32,453 --> 00:52:34,330
Alright, I see.

839
00:52:34,330 --> 00:52:35,748
Have a good meal.

840
00:52:35,748 --> 00:52:37,866
<i>- Thanks!</i>
- Sure.

841
00:53:16,914 --> 00:53:18,958
I'll get a menu ready for you.

842
00:53:18,958 --> 00:53:19,958
Thank you.

843
00:53:19,958 --> 00:53:21,292
If you need anything...

844
00:53:21,292 --> 00:53:24,200
Oh no, I'll order once my date gets here.

845
00:53:48,821 --> 00:53:51,158
Here's the wine you ordered.

846
00:53:54,076 --> 00:53:55,625
What's this?

847
00:53:55,625 --> 00:53:57,639
The gentleman over there ordered it.

848
00:54:05,170 --> 00:54:06,859
That's already the third bottle.

849
00:54:06,859 --> 00:54:09,125
- Care for a tasting?
- No thanks.

850
00:54:09,125 --> 00:54:10,467
Excuse me.

851
00:54:10,467 --> 00:54:12,333
Pour his glass all the way up,

852
00:54:12,333 --> 00:54:14,042
and just a splash for us.

853
00:54:14,042 --> 00:54:15,729
Got it.

854
00:54:25,374 --> 00:54:27,450
Let me take these extra glasses.

855
00:54:30,115 --> 00:54:31,333
Na Hui,

856
00:54:31,333 --> 00:54:34,293
we're leaving right after this dessert.

857
00:54:34,293 --> 00:54:35,992
What?

858
00:54:36,586 --> 00:54:38,667
Hurry, grab the bill before more wine comes.

859
00:54:38,667 --> 00:54:40,742
Oh, okay.

860
00:54:48,292 --> 00:54:51,875
He seriously does not know when to quit.

861
00:54:52,509 --> 00:54:54,375
He always has to cross the line.

862
00:54:54,375 --> 00:54:56,575
I should've never made peace with him.

863
00:55:03,436 --> 00:55:06,783
<i>I think I just got dumped.</i>

864
00:55:10,151 --> 00:55:12,158
<i>What do you mean?</i>

865
00:55:13,779 --> 00:55:15,944
<i>PD Shin bailed on our plans.</i>

866
00:55:15,944 --> 00:55:18,200
<i>At the very last minute.</i>

867
00:55:19,660 --> 00:55:21,537
What? Out of nowhere?

868
00:55:21,537 --> 00:55:24,167
Luche Vino.

869
00:55:24,167 --> 00:55:26,750
The restaurant's name is Luche Vino.

870
00:55:26,750 --> 00:55:29,003
It's right next to Writer Kim's studio.

871
00:55:29,003 --> 00:55:30,921
You know it, right?

872
00:55:30,921 --> 00:55:33,048
Right, that place.

873
00:55:33,048 --> 00:55:35,450
Anyway, I'm here, so...

874
00:55:39,805 --> 00:55:42,224
Just get over here for now.

875
00:55:42,224 --> 00:55:44,825
<i>He canceled right before?</i>

876
00:55:45,958 --> 00:55:50,983
<i>Yes, I'm eating by myself right now.</i>

877
00:55:50,983 --> 00:55:54,375
What the heck is going on?

878
00:55:54,375 --> 00:55:56,575
<i>What was his reason?</i>

879
00:56:01,660 --> 00:56:04,367
Isn't that PD Shin over there?

880
00:56:07,458 --> 00:56:09,783
Why is he here?

881
00:56:11,462 --> 00:56:14,783
<i>I don't know, he just said he was sorry...</i>

882
00:56:19,094 --> 00:56:21,198
Why is he here?

883
00:56:22,890 --> 00:56:24,658
Got it.

884
00:56:27,520 --> 00:56:29,313
Evening, Writer Kim.

885
00:56:29,313 --> 00:56:31,033
What?

886
00:56:32,583 --> 00:56:35,083
What are you doing out here?

887
00:56:35,083 --> 00:56:37,321
How did you even get here?

888
00:56:37,321 --> 00:56:40,199
They said you took off for another thing.

889
00:56:40,199 --> 00:56:42,660
Plans fell through.

890
00:56:42,660 --> 00:56:44,375
I talked to Na Hui on the phone,

891
00:56:44,375 --> 00:56:47,706
and she said you all ended up here.

892
00:56:47,706 --> 00:56:49,333
I thought I'd stop by to see you.

893
00:56:49,333 --> 00:56:51,950
Plus I still haven't had dinner.

894
00:56:53,312 --> 00:56:55,297
It's not too late to order?

895
00:56:55,297 --> 00:56:57,242
I'm really hungry.

896
00:57:04,640 --> 00:57:06,825
Are you keeping tabs on me?

897
00:57:07,643 --> 00:57:09,603
Here to play watchdog as usual.

898
00:57:09,603 --> 00:57:12,033
Popping up out of nowhere like this.

899
00:57:14,608 --> 00:57:19,325
I'm about to lose it, seriously.

900
00:57:22,333 --> 00:57:24,792
What's going on between them?

901
00:57:24,792 --> 00:57:27,162
Writer Kim Ju Ho seems really angry.

902
00:57:27,162 --> 00:57:29,867
Yeah, seriously.

903
00:57:36,000 --> 00:57:38,799
What am I supposed to do with you?

904
00:57:38,799 --> 00:57:42,700
Getting under my skin since Busan, damn.

905
00:57:47,640 --> 00:57:50,667
- What is your problem with me?
- Vintage wine.

906
00:57:50,667 --> 00:57:52,812
<i>Stop. That's enough.</i>

907
00:57:52,812 --> 00:57:55,292
What? Vintage wine?

908
00:57:55,292 --> 00:57:56,441
What about the vintage wine?

909
00:57:56,441 --> 00:57:58,408
Vintage wine is

910
00:57:59,152 --> 00:58:01,250
that's your move, right?

911
00:58:01,250 --> 00:58:02,250
What do you mean?

912
00:58:02,250 --> 00:58:06,276
You always open with vintage wine
when you make a move.

913
00:58:06,276 --> 00:58:08,208
Whenever you're interested
in a woman from work,

914
00:58:08,208 --> 00:58:10,766
you always pull out that vintage wine move.

915
00:58:10,766 --> 00:58:12,123
Well...

916
00:58:12,123 --> 00:58:15,501
I've personally witnessed this five times.

917
00:58:15,501 --> 00:58:19,005
Most recently it was that girl
from the ball club?

918
00:58:19,005 --> 00:58:21,340
And the translator, wait,

919
00:58:21,340 --> 00:58:23,968
the editor from the Japanese publisher too.

920
00:58:23,968 --> 00:58:26,262
It's always the vintage wine first,

921
00:58:26,262 --> 00:58:27,792
bringing up the year on the label,

922
00:58:27,792 --> 00:58:29,333
wanting to "bond over memories,"

923
00:58:29,333 --> 00:58:32,033
and it never ended well.

924
00:58:32,852 --> 00:58:35,825
You even dumped the fallout on me before.

925
00:58:38,625 --> 00:58:40,589
You're really just going to spill all this?

926
00:58:40,589 --> 00:58:43,125
<i>Right, that's enough talking.</i>

927
00:58:43,125 --> 00:58:44,530
The editor probably

928
00:58:44,530 --> 00:58:47,074
has no idea about any of this.

929
00:58:47,074 --> 00:58:49,492
Since I never said a word.

930
00:58:50,203 --> 00:58:53,206
But if the editor found out,

931
00:58:53,206 --> 00:58:56,325
he'd never push you on Writer Kim.

932
00:58:58,544 --> 00:59:01,375
I'm Writer Kim's assigned producer,

933
00:59:01,375 --> 00:59:04,634
and the second you pulled out that wine,

934
00:59:04,634 --> 00:59:09,075
I had every reason to be concerned.

935
00:59:16,771 --> 00:59:19,042
Want me to go out there?

936
00:59:19,042 --> 00:59:20,107
Yeah, sure.

937
00:59:20,107 --> 00:59:22,867
No, wait, actually, I'll go.

938
00:59:28,074 --> 00:59:30,493
Oh, you hit me?

939
00:59:30,493 --> 00:59:32,658
I can't believe you just hit me.

940
00:59:33,579 --> 00:59:36,457
This little... seriously, hey!

941
00:59:36,457 --> 00:59:38,917
You really want to do this?

942
00:59:38,917 --> 00:59:40,375
Hey, my glasses!

943
00:59:40,375 --> 00:59:42,783
Damn it!

944
00:59:49,095 --> 00:59:51,143
I can't believe this.

945
00:59:54,708 --> 00:59:55,958
Damn it!

946
00:59:55,958 --> 00:59:57,875
Let go! Hey, let go of me!

947
00:59:57,875 --> 00:59:59,083
What's wrong with them?

948
01:00:01,274 --> 01:00:02,334
Hey, let go!

949
01:00:02,334 --> 01:00:04,075
Let go, you...

950
01:00:23,754 --> 01:00:26,408
- What are they doing?
- Stop it, please!

951
01:00:27,625 --> 01:00:29,992
Come on, seriously.

952
01:00:31,375 --> 01:00:34,958
Oh no, go stop them! They've lost their minds!

953
01:00:36,083 --> 01:00:37,100
What?

954
01:00:37,100 --> 01:00:38,744
Looks like there's a fight.

955
01:00:47,444 --> 01:00:49,333
That's enough.

956
01:00:49,333 --> 01:00:51,198
Let go of me!

957
01:00:51,198 --> 01:00:52,250
Seriously!

958
01:00:52,250 --> 01:00:55,125
Let me go! It's him, not me!
I didn't start this!

959
01:00:55,125 --> 01:00:56,542
Get your hands off me!

960
01:00:56,542 --> 01:00:57,708
You little... damn!

961
01:00:57,708 --> 01:01:00,859
Stop it! What are you doing?

962
01:01:01,875 --> 01:01:04,117
Seriously.

963
01:01:06,213 --> 01:01:09,758
Just let me go. I'll use words! Okay, I'm done!

964
01:01:09,758 --> 01:01:11,867
Seriously.

965
01:01:13,583 --> 01:01:15,875
Enough! Cut it out!

966
01:01:15,875 --> 01:01:17,333
That's enough!

967
01:01:17,333 --> 01:01:18,934
Enough!

968
01:01:18,934 --> 01:01:20,658
Enough!

969
01:01:22,708 --> 01:01:24,625
That's it.

970
01:01:29,194 --> 01:01:30,570
Oh, damn.

971
01:01:30,570 --> 01:01:32,283
Just let me go already.

972
01:01:48,672 --> 01:01:50,833
Please, go on in.

973
01:01:50,833 --> 01:01:53,417
You don't need to deal with this.
I'll sort it out.

974
01:01:53,417 --> 01:01:54,583
What just happened?

975
01:01:54,583 --> 01:01:58,181
I'm completely lost right now, honestly.

976
01:01:58,181 --> 01:02:00,167
Yeah, I know, right?

977
01:02:00,167 --> 01:02:03,200
But how did you end up here?

978
01:02:04,625 --> 01:02:07,208
I'm the one who called Ju Ho.

979
01:02:07,208 --> 01:02:08,750
I told him to come see you.

980
01:02:08,750 --> 01:02:11,486
I figured a group dinner
would smooth things over...

981
01:02:11,486 --> 01:02:14,436
It's completely on me. I apologize.

982
01:02:14,436 --> 01:02:18,309
It's not like you saw this coming.

983
01:02:18,309 --> 01:02:19,333
Please go in.

984
01:02:19,333 --> 01:02:21,575
I'll call you later.

985
01:02:24,458 --> 01:02:25,959
Gosh, I was terrified.

986
01:02:25,959 --> 01:02:27,875
I felt like I was watching a live play.

987
01:02:27,875 --> 01:02:30,333
They rushed on stage, then rushed right off.

988
01:02:30,333 --> 01:02:32,583
- They were kicking and...
- Are you enjoying this?

989
01:02:32,583 --> 01:02:34,408
I'm sorry.

990
01:02:35,616 --> 01:02:37,783
Goodness.

991
01:03:42,910 --> 01:03:46,367
<i>You're done for. Completely done for.</i>

992
01:04:42,052 --> 01:04:44,429
<i>You messed up beyond repair.</i>

993
01:04:44,429 --> 01:04:47,006
<i>So what's the plan now?</i>

994
01:04:59,375 --> 01:05:03,325
[Editor An Dae Yong]

995
01:05:14,114 --> 01:05:15,126
Hello?

996
01:05:15,126 --> 01:05:17,044
<i>Dude, have you lost it?</i>

997
01:05:17,044 --> 01:05:18,880
<i>Unbelievable.</i>

998
01:05:18,880 --> 01:05:21,340
I moved you to a new team
and you still cause trouble?

999
01:05:21,340 --> 01:05:25,136
Since when do you throw fists at your seniors?

1000
01:05:25,136 --> 01:05:26,429
I...

1001
01:05:26,429 --> 01:05:28,181
didn't do anything.

1002
01:05:28,181 --> 01:05:30,266
- He's the one who started it.
<i>- Zip it.</i>

1003
01:05:30,266 --> 01:05:33,269
Unless you want to lose your job,
get here and say sorry.

1004
01:05:33,269 --> 01:05:36,439
I'm at his studio right now, so get over here.

1005
01:05:36,439 --> 01:05:38,458
I'm sorry.

1006
01:05:38,458 --> 01:05:39,542
But it wasn't my...

1007
01:05:39,542 --> 01:05:42,000
I said don't argue about who's right.

1008
01:05:42,000 --> 01:05:44,405
Sort that out later. Just apologize first.

1009
01:05:44,405 --> 01:05:46,158
Get here right now.

1010
01:06:23,917 --> 01:06:25,825
Yes, it's me.

1011
01:06:26,781 --> 01:06:28,867
Yeah.

1012
01:06:30,258 --> 01:06:32,658
And what about PD Shin...

1013
01:06:33,309 --> 01:06:34,958
I told him to come apologize right away.

1014
01:06:34,958 --> 01:06:36,457
He'll be coming here.

1015
01:06:36,457 --> 01:06:38,417
I have to get them to patch things up today.

1016
01:06:38,417 --> 01:06:40,419
So what started the whole fight?

1017
01:06:40,419 --> 01:06:42,208
I'm just as clueless as you are.

1018
01:06:42,208 --> 01:06:44,200
He's not talking.

1019
01:06:48,333 --> 01:06:49,375
Okay.

1020
01:06:49,375 --> 01:06:51,388
I'll call you back.

1021
01:06:51,388 --> 01:06:53,825
<i>- Oh, sure.</i>
- Yeah.

1022
01:06:55,583 --> 01:06:57,450
Who is it?

1023
01:07:10,917 --> 01:07:13,242
PD Shin.

1024
01:07:14,578 --> 01:07:18,039
I figured you'd go to Writer Kim Ju Ho first.

1025
01:07:18,039 --> 01:07:20,242
What are you doing here?

1026
01:07:21,418 --> 01:07:24,242
I thought I should come to you first.

1027
01:07:25,005 --> 01:07:26,783
What for?

1028
01:07:29,426 --> 01:07:31,450
What brings you here?

1029
01:07:34,306 --> 01:07:36,242
I'm not sure.

1030
01:07:37,684 --> 01:07:40,117
You don't know?

1031
01:07:42,397 --> 01:07:43,899
I really don't.

1032
01:07:43,899 --> 01:07:45,783
I can't explain it myself.

1033
01:07:48,320 --> 01:07:51,450
Why did you blow off your date with Jenny?

1034
01:07:52,115 --> 01:07:54,033
I don't know.

1035
01:07:54,868 --> 01:07:57,575
You don't know that either?

1036
01:07:59,372 --> 01:08:01,082
I shouldn't have done that.

1037
01:08:01,082 --> 01:08:03,908
Exactly, you shouldn't do that.

1038
01:08:10,926 --> 01:08:14,492
Is that what you're here to say sorry for?

1039
01:08:16,250 --> 01:08:18,958
Don't worry about me, just go take care of...

1040
01:08:18,958 --> 01:08:21,325
That's not why I'm here.

1041
01:08:29,903 --> 01:08:31,742
Then what?

1042
01:08:35,951 --> 01:08:38,575
I think I might

1043
01:08:44,648 --> 01:08:46,908
have feelings for you.

1044
01:09:26,833 --> 01:09:28,895
[The pretty girl who buys you food]

1045
01:09:45,542 --> 01:09:48,333
<i>What has gotten into him?</i>

1046
01:09:48,333 --> 01:09:50,626
<i>Everyone, it's an emergency!</i>

1047
01:09:50,626 --> 01:09:52,368
<i>- I'll fix this!
- Grab him!</i>

1048
01:09:52,368 --> 01:09:54,292
<i>Yumi set us up without knowing, so...</i>

1049
01:09:54,292 --> 01:09:56,750
<i>It's over and done with between them.</i>

1050
01:09:56,750 --> 01:09:58,875
<i>We're giving all our love to PD Shin.</i>

1051
01:09:58,875 --> 01:10:01,667
<i>Heart Fever Time!</i>

1052
01:10:01,667 --> 01:10:03,250
<i>PD Shin, come this way.</i>

1053
01:10:03,250 --> 01:10:05,533
<i>Go, PD Shin, go!</i>

1054
01:10:07,500 --> 01:10:08,542
<i>PD Shin?</i>

1055
01:10:08,542 --> 01:10:10,000
<i>What brings you here?</i>

1056
01:10:10,000 --> 01:10:12,950
<i>It's the same thing all over again.</i>
